Russia Meets 9.7% of Spring Grain Sowing Target, Ministry Says

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-04-29T12:03:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/russia-meets-9-7-of-spring-grain-sowing-target-ministry-says.html
Russian farmers planted 2.9 million
hectares with spring grains as of today, or 9.7 percent of the
target, the Agriculture Ministry said on its  website .  Total sowings of all crops, including grains and other
plantings, were 4.8 million hectares, or 9.5 percent of the
planned 50.4 million hectares, the ministry said.  The condition of  Russia ’s winter crops is “good” and no
more than the annual average will perish, according to the
report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow 
